    "To aid split operations, we implemented an algorithm that uses a small number of locations coarsely surrounding the merge error, making the resulting topology of the split robust to the precise location or number of labels (Fig. 2f and Extended Data Fig.",
    "Split operations are always executed locally, and a user may need to execute multiple split operations to separate two cell segments that were falsely merged in multiple places.",
    "To speed up merging of many fragments, we added a multimerge operation to neuroglancer, allowing users to execute merge operations in parallel.",
    "We measured view and edit performances during real-world proofreading of the ChunkedGraph v2 on the MICrONS65 dataset, the largest currently available, and the FlyWire dataset, which we could use for comparison with the original implementation.",
    "For viewing the segmentation, the user selects a supervoxel by clicking a location in space, and the system retrieves all supervoxels that belong to the same segment f, To submit a split operation, users place labels for each side of the split (top right)."
